h.rs and timeout_cancel.rs have no fee calculation |\n| 5 | Either player can trigger timeout cancel | SATISFIED | timeout_cancel.rs caller == creator OR opponent |\n\n### FR-5: Fairness Verification\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Completed match displays VRF seed/proof details | SATISFIED | MatchSettled event emits randomness bytes + vrf_request_key (state.rs:63, claim_payout.rs:163). ActiveMatchView shows randomness hex, derived result, VRF fulfillment status after \"Verify Fairness\" click. |\n| 2 | Players can independently verify result matches VRF | SATISFIED | verification.ts:verifyMatch() re-derives result from Orao randomness via from_randomness(byte[0] % 2), compares to event winner, confirms Orao account fulfillment. |\n| 3 | Verification accessible from match history and result screen | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView \"Verify Fairness\" button (post-claim). FairnessPage (/fairness) allows paste-a-tx-signature verification for any match. |\n\n### FR-6: Lobby Browser UI\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Open games list shows creator name/avatar, tier, amount, side, join button | SATISFIED | MatchCard.tsx:13 (PlayerAvatar:25, getDisplayName:28, tier:50, amount:41, side:36, join:57) |\n| 2 | Filter by tier | SATISFIED | OpenMatchesList.tsx:43 `matches.filter(m => m.tier === selectedTier)` |\n| 3 | Sort by newest/oldest/amount | SATISFIED | OpenMatchesList.tsx:18 sortMatches, :79 select dropdown |\n| 4 | Create Game panel with tier selection grid and Heads/Tails toggle | SATISFIED | CoinflipPage.tsx sidebar: TierSelector + CoinSideSelector.tsx:19 |\n| 5 | Estimated wait time (deferred if data unavailable) | DEFERRED | Self-deferred in criterion text (\"deferred to post-MVP polish if data unavailable\"). Requires match fill-rate analytics infrastructure. |\n\n### FR-7: Active Game and Result UI\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Both players shown with avatars, names, wager amounts | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView.tsx:88-108 PlayerAvatarCompact, side labels, entry amount |\n| 2 | 3D coin flip animation with multiple rotations and gradual slowdown | SATISFIED | CoinAnimation.tsx:20 CSS 3D transform (front/back faces :53-58), spinning classes :43-45 |\n| 3 | Winning side highlighted with glow effect | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView.tsx:200-205 result color + textShadow glow |\n| 4 | \"YOU WIN!\" or \"YOU LOSE\" overlay displayed | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView.tsx:128 \"You Won!\", :129-139 \"You Lost\" with heart+shards animation |\n| 5 | Payout amount shown for winner | SATISFIED | ActiveMatchView.tsx:207-210 `match.payoutAmount.toFixed(4) SOL` |\n| 6 | Quick rematch option available after result | SATISFIED | \"Play Again\" button in ActiveMatchView post-claim section. Calls createMatch with same tier/side. Opponent must find and join from lobby. |\n\n### FR-8: Audio Feedback\n\n| # | Criterion | Status | Evidence |\n|---|-----------|--------|----------|\n| 1 | Coin flip spinning sound during animation | DEFERRED | Scope Decisions: \"Deferred to later spec: Audio integration...\" |\n| 2 | Dramatic pause before landing | DEFERRED | Same reference. |\n| 3 | Victory sound for winner | DEFERRED | Same reference. |\n| 4 | Coin clink on landing | DEFERRED | Same reference. |\n\n## Gap Summary\n\n| # | FR | Criterion | Severity | Category | Blocked By | Next Step |\n|---|-----|-----------|----------|----------|------------|-----------|\n| — | — | — | — | — | — | **All implementation gaps resolved.** Only deferred items remain. |\n\n## Resolved Items\n\n| Item | Resolution | Date |\n|------|-----------|------|\n| VRF oracle/resolver (FR-3.1, FR-3.2) | Orao VRF integrated via shared vrf_orao module. join_match embeds VRF request CPI; claim_payout reads randomness at claim time. 3-tx flow: create→join(+VRF)→claim(+settle). Previous MagicBlock VRF and resolve_match instruction deleted in 004 rewrite. | 2026-02-26 |\n| VRF reproducibility (FR-3.3) | from_randomness(byte) is pure deterministic (constants.rs:15). verification.ts re-derives result from Orao randomness bytes. Orao randomness account persists on-chain for proof. | 2026-02-26 |\n| VRF seed/proof display (FR-5.1) | MatchSettled event emits randomness bytes + vrf_request_key. ActiveMatchView displays verification details after \"Verify Fairness\" click. | 2026-02-26 |\n| Independent verification (FR-5.2) | verification.ts:verifyMatch() fetches tx, extracts MatchSettled event, re-derives result, confirms Orao account fulfillment. | 2026-02-26 |\n| Verification accessibility (FR-5.3) | \"Verify Fairness\" button in ActiveMatchView (post-claim). FairnessPage (/fairness) supports paste-a-tx-signature verification. | 2026-02-26 |\n| Quick rematch (FR-7.6) | \"Play Again\" button in ActiveMatchView. Creates new open match with same tier/side via existing createMatch action. | 2026-02-26 |\n| Timeout safety net | timeout_cancel instruction: either player can cancel LOCKED match after 2 min timeout if VRF unfulfilled. Refunds both players. Uses shared::timeout::is_expired + shared::vrf_orao::is_fulfilled guards. | 2026-02-19 |\n| Claimable matches | fetchClaimableMatches() in chain.ts with dual memcmp queries (creator/opponent). \"Your Matches\" section in CoinflipPage with claim/cancel/view actions. | 2026-02-26 |\n\n## Deferred Items\n\n| Item | Deferred To | Target Spec | Target Status | Stale? |\n|------|-------------|-------------|---------------|--------|\n| Estimated wait time (FR-6.5) | post-MVP polish | none specified | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Spinning sound (FR-8.1) | later spec | dedicated audio spec | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Dramatic pause sound (FR-8.2) | later spec | dedicated audio spec | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Victory sound (FR-8.3) | later spec | dedicated audio spec | — | UNTRACKED |\n| Coin clink sound (FR-8.4) | later spec | dedicated audio spec | — | UNTRACKED |\n\n5 deferred items remain. All FR-5 and FR-7.6 items previously deferred are now **RESOLVED**.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Audio spec**: All 4 FR-8 items should be bundled into a dedicated audio/SFX spec covering sound design across all games. Low priority for launch.\n\n2. **Estimated wait time (FR-6.5)**: Self-deferred and low priority. Requires match fill-rate analytics data that doesn't exist yet. Safe to keep deferred past launch.\n\n3. **Frontend test coverage**: Zero vitest/component tests and zero Playwright E2E tests exist. Not an FR criterion but notable for launch readiness. Consider adding to E2E integration spec (203).\n","numLines":223,"startLine":1,"totalLines":223}}}
